z-Faria|2007}}}}\n{{refend}}\n\n===Journals===\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite journal|last=Wanger|first=G\u00fcnther A.|title=Radiometric dating of the type-site for Homo heidelbergensis at Mauer, Germany|doi=10.1073/pnas.1012722107|pmid=21041630|volume=107|issue=46|pages=19726\u201319730|journal=Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences|ref={{sfnref|Wagner|2010}}|pmc=2993404|year=2010|bibcode=2010PNAS..10719726W}}\n* {{cite journal|last=Bordewich|first=Fergus M.|title=The Ambush That Changed History: An amateur archaeologist discovers the field where wily Germanic warriors halted the spread of the Roman Empire|url=http://www.smithsonianmag.com/history-archaeology/ambush.html#ixzz1E6QmkvIw|journal=[[Smithsonian (magazine)|Smithsonian magazine]]|date=September 2005|ref={{sfnref|Smithsonian (September 2005)}}}}\n* {{cite journal|first=Loyd E.|last=Lee|title=The German Confederation and the Consolidation of State Power in the South German States, 1815\u20131848|journal=Consortium on Revolutionary Europe 1750\u20131850: Proceedings|year=1985|volume=15|ref={{sfnref|Lee|1985}}}}\n{{refend}}\n\n===Atlas and maps===\n* [https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Atlas_of_Germany ''Atlas of Germany''] Wikipedia maps; not copyright\n\n==Further reading==\n\n===Surveys===\n* Biesinger, Joseph A. ''Germany: a reference guide from the Renaissance to the present'' (2006)\n* Bithell, Jethro, ed. ''Germany: A Companion to German Studies'' (5th ed. 1955), 578pp; essays on German literature, music, philosophy, art and, especially, history. [https://www.questia.com/library/book/germany-a-companion-to-german-studies-by-jethro-bithell.jsp online edition]\n* B\u00f6sch, Frank. ''Mass Media and Historical Change: Germany in International Perspective, 1400 to the Present'' (Berghahn, 2015). 212 pp. [https://networks.h-net.org/node/35008/reviews/132865/seul-b%C3%B6sch-mass-media-and-historical-change-germany-international online review]\n* Buse, Dieter K. ed. ''Modern Germany: An Encyclopedia of His